---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Electrolux Refrigerator Repair | Southern California | French Door";
const description = "Electrolux refrigerator repair across Southern California — French Door, Counter-Depth, Perfect Temp Drawer, ICON legacy. Swedish parent (Frigidaire subsidiary). $89 diagnostic. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/electrolux-refrigerator-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Electrolux the same company as Frigidaire, or are they different brands?",
    a: "Different brands, same parent company, shared engineering platforms — and this is one of the most important service-side facts about Electrolux refrigerators in the US. AB Electrolux is a Swedish multinational (headquartered in Stockholm, founded 1919) that acquired Frigidaire in 1986 to establish its US manufacturing and distribution footprint. Today Electrolux-branded refrigerators and Frigidaire-branded refrigerators are manufactured on shared platforms in the same US plants (primarily Electrolux's Anderson, SC facility and other American factories). The tiering: Electrolux is the premium tier, Frigidaire is the mass-market tier; Frigidaire Professional sits between them. Shared platforms mean shared sealed-system components, shared compressor specs on certain SKUs, and shared service tools. For our techs, an Electrolux French Door service call and a Frigidaire Professional French Door service call look similar under the hood; the cabinet finish, trim, and electronics differ, but the refrigeration architecture is often the same. Parts cross-compatibility is real on certain components, though not all — we always source Electrolux-specific parts for Electrolux-branded units to preserve exact factory spec."
  },
  {
    q: "We bought an Electrolux ICON refrigerator — do you still service those?",
    a: "Yes, and that's a question we field regularly. Electrolux ICON was the discontinued premium-premium tier above standard Electrolux — counter-depth French Door, higher-spec stainless, upgraded trim — marketed from the mid-2000s and discontinued in the US market around 2020. The installed base is still substantial in LA kitchens from that era. Service on ICON is largely unchanged from the mainstream Electrolux line of the same generation: shared sealed-system components, shared compressor platforms, shared service architecture. Parts availability on ICON-specific trim and handle hardware has tightened since discontinuation — some aesthetic components are end-of-production and require aftermarket or secondary sourcing. Refrigeration-cycle and sealed-system parts still flow through Electrolux's US parts channel without issue. If your ICON has a fault that requires a discontinued trim piece, we'll tell you straight whether the repair pencils against the available options; if it's refrigeration-side, service runs at normal pace."
  },
  {
    q: "What is Perfect Temp and how does it affect repair diagnostics?",
    a: "Perfect Temp is Electrolux's signature full-width temperature-controlled drawer — one of the most distinctive features of the Electrolux French Door line. It's a wide drawer that spans the full cabinet width (wider than a standard crisper), with electronic temperature control from about 28°F (meat/chill) through 42°F (produce), independent airflow from the main fresh-food compartment. The drawer has its own temperature sensor, its own airflow baffle, and on some SKUs its own defrost routing. Service implication: Perfect Temp symptoms don't always trace back to the main fridge. A homeowner reporting \"my meat is freezing in the bottom drawer\" or \"produce is wilting in the chill drawer\" is typically describing Perfect Temp-specific issues, not whole-fridge issues. Diagnostic order: verify the drawer mode setpoint, read the Perfect Temp sensor via the Electrolux service interface, check the airflow baffle for frost, inspect the drain routing if moisture is accumulating. Sensor replacement $180–$320; airflow-baffle service $160–$260."
  },
  {
    q: "Our Electrolux French Door has a water dispenser that stopped working — common?",
    a: "Yes, fairly common, and the fix depends on which stage of the water path has failed. Electrolux water dispensers route from the supply line through a fill valve, through a water filter housing, through a chilled water reservoir (on units with chilled-water spec), through the dispenser nozzle with a solenoid that opens when you press the dispenser lever. Our diagnostic order: test water supply pressure at the fridge inlet, inspect the filter (scaled or expired filters block flow), verify the valve solenoid opens on command, check the dispenser-switch continuity, and finally the reservoir integrity. The most common faults we see: scaled fill valve (LA hard-water households), expired water filter nobody replaced, and stuck dispenser solenoid. Fill-valve replacement $240–$360. Filter replacement $40–$80 parts (standard filter, homeowner-installable). Dispenser solenoid $180–$280."
  },
  {
    q: "Do Electrolux and Frigidaire share the same compressor? That would affect repair cost.",
    a: "Often yes on the platform level, though specific part numbers can differ. AB Electrolux's US-market refrigerator lineup (Electrolux, Frigidaire, Frigidaire Professional, Gallery) shares compressor families across tier points — the physical compressor on an Electrolux Counter-Depth French Door is frequently the same class and often the same exact SKU as the compressor on a Frigidaire Professional Counter-Depth French Door of the same generation. The cost implication: post-warranty compressor replacement on an Electrolux is priced similarly to the same job on Frigidaire Professional; the compressor part itself is available through the shared Electrolux parts channel. Our techs confirm the exact compressor spec before ordering to ensure factory-exact match, but the pricing runs consistent across the shared-platform siblings. Compressor replacement $900–$1,600 depending on SKU and refrigerant. What differs across the tier points: cabinet finish, trim hardware, electronics sophistication, and warranty coverage — but not the core refrigeration guts in most cases."
  },
  {
    q: "Is Electrolux Professional the same as Electrolux residential?",
    a: "No — and this is a frequent-confusion point we clarify on service calls. Electrolux Professional is a separate publicly-traded company that was spun off from AB Electrolux in March 2020. It focuses on commercial foodservice equipment (commercial dishwashers, commercial laundry, commercial food prep) and operates with its own product lines, service network, and parts channel. Electrolux Professional is NOT the same entity as the AB Electrolux that owns residential Electrolux and Frigidaire in the US. If you have a commercial dishwasher at a restaurant and it says \"Electrolux Professional\" — different company, different service. If you have a residential French Door fridge that says \"Electrolux\" — that's AB Electrolux's consumer line, serviced by our team. We service the residential side; for Electrolux Professional commercial equipment, the factory-authorized commercial service network is the right path."
  },
  {
    q: "Our Electrolux fridge ice-maker just stopped — is this the usual LA hard-water story?",
    a: "Often, yes. Electrolux French Door ice-makers are subject to the same LA hard-water pattern that affects every ice-maker in Encino, Sherman Oaks, Tarzana, Calabasas, Pasadena — fill valve scales, water flow drops, ice-mold fills partially, ice production declines. Descaling plus fill-valve inspection resolves most cases. Electrolux revised the ice-maker module on several French Door SKUs in the 2018–2020 generation with better scale tolerance; if your unit is earlier-generation and in a hard-water neighborhood, the revised module is occasionally worth considering on heavy-ice households. Standard descale + valve service $280–$440. Module replacement if warranted $420–$620. The Electrolux ice-maker architecture is shared with Frigidaire Professional, so parts availability is strong across the family."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Electrolux refrigerator repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Common Electrolux bands: door gasket (French Door) $220–$400; door gasket (Counter-Depth built-in-style) $260–$440; Perfect Temp drawer sensor or airflow service $180–$320; water dispenser fill valve $240–$360; dispenser solenoid $180–$280; ice-maker fill valve + descaling $280–$440; condenser fan motor $260–$440; evaporator fan $240–$400; defrost heater and thermostat $280–$480; main control board $440–$720; water filter replacement (homeowner-installable standard filter) $40–$80 parts; compressor replacement (post-warranty, shared Electrolux-Frigidaire platform) $900–$1,600; full ice-maker module replacement $420–$620. ICON-specific trim hardware (for discontinued-tier service) runs higher on parts cost due to tightened availability. Parts lead times typically 1–2 weeks through the Electrolux US parts channel; stocked common items same-week."
  },
  {
    q: "Swedish engineering — does that mean anything real for the US-market Electrolux fridge?",
    a: "Some, not everything. AB Electrolux does genuine product engineering in Sweden (Stockholm HQ plus Scandinavian R&D centers) for the global residential lineup, and design language and energy-efficiency philosophy trace back to Scandinavian engineering sensibilities. For the US-market fridge specifically though, the product is manufactured in US plants, engineered with US-market feature requirements (ice-makers, water dispensers, counter-depth form factors that are less common in Europe), and tuned to US electrical spec. So what you're getting is Swedish-heritage brand engineering philosophy applied to a US-manufactured product optimized for US kitchens. Practically for service: parts chain and service network are US-based, not international. Service quality doesn't depend on Swedish-parts flow; it depends on the US Electrolux parts distribution and authorized service infrastructure."
  },
  {
    q: "Is our Electrolux French Door under any factory warranty we should know about?",
    a: "Depends on when it was purchased and how you registered it. Current Electrolux refrigerator factory warranty is generally 1 year full parts and labor, extended to longer terms on the sealed-system components (compressor, evaporator, condenser) — typically 5 years parts-only, sometimes longer on premium tiers. ICON and older premium Electrolux models from before the line was streamlined had different warranty structures. Extended manufacturer warranties (1 year additional via registration, plus retail-extended warranties) are common on Electrolux purchases, which is why we ask at dispatch whether the homeowner has factory or third-party warranty documentation. If warranty applies, factory-authorized service is the right path; we can coordinate the warranty-claim check or hand off. Out of warranty, our team handles the repair directly with genuine Electrolux parts."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Electrolux Refrigerator Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical,
    "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL,
    "priceRange": "$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "Electrolux Refrigerator Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Electrolux refrigerator repair across Los Angeles — French Door, Counter-Depth, Side-by-Side, Perfect Temp full-width drawer, water dispenser and ice-maker service, shared Electrolux-Frigidaire platform compressor service, ICON legacy-tier coverage. AB Electrolux Swedish parent, Frigidaire subsidiary since 1986. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": f.q,
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a }
    }))
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Electrolux", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/electrolux/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Electrolux Refrigerator Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <div class="call-banner">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>Electrolux fridge acting up? Same-day service across LA:</span>
      <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
          <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Electrolux › Refrigerator Repair</div>
          <h1>Electrolux Refrigerator Repair</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            Electrolux is the Swedish-parent residential refrigerator brand AB Electrolux built in the US on the
            Frigidaire manufacturing infrastructure acquired in 1986. Our techs service the full Electrolux
            lineup: Counter-Depth French Door, full-depth French Door, Side-by-Side, the signature Perfect Temp
            full-width drawer, water-dispensing ice-and-water systems, and the discontinued Electrolux ICON tier
            for legacy installs. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
            <a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="hero-facts">
            <li><b>Perfect Temp drawer diagnostic depth</b> — sensor vs airflow vs drain</li>
            <li><b>Electrolux-Frigidaire shared-platform parts</b> — US channel, 1–2 week typical</li>
            <li><b>ICON legacy support</b> — discontinued-tier service through aftermarket sourcing</li>
            <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b> — waived when you authorize the repair</li>
          </ul>
        </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>CSLB #1138898 · Insured</span>
      <span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span>
      <span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Electrolux in LA — the Swedish brand built on US Frigidaire infrastructure</h2>
      <p>
        AB Electrolux is a Swedish multinational founded in Stockholm in 1919. Its US presence runs through the
        Frigidaire acquisition in 1986 — when Electrolux bought Frigidaire (founded 1918 in Fort Wayne, Indiana),
        the deal gave the Swedish parent an established US manufacturing footprint, a US parts and service network,
        and a mass-market refrigerator brand positioned below the Electrolux-branded premium line. Today, US-market
        Electrolux and Frigidaire refrigerators are manufactured on shared platforms across US plants (primarily
        Anderson, SC plus other facilities). Electrolux is the premium tier, Frigidaire Professional sits in the
        middle, and Frigidaire is the mass-market tier. That platform sharing is load-bearing for our techs'
        understanding of the brand — when we open an Electrolux French Door and a Frigidaire Professional French
        Door of similar generation, the refrigeration architecture often looks nearly identical.
      </p>
      <p>
        The LA Electrolux households we serve are split between two main cohorts. First: 2008–2018 premium kitchen
        remodels that specified Electrolux or Electrolux ICON as the premium-without-Sub-Zero-pricing choice —
        these units are still running in Westside condos, Beverly Hills renovations, and Pasadena homes. Second:
        current-generation Electrolux Counter-Depth French Door in newer renovations where the homeowner picked
        Electrolux for energy efficiency and Perfect Temp feature set over the Sub-Zero or Thermador alternatives
        at much higher price points. Our team services both generations; parts availability on current units is
        strong through the Electrolux US channel, and legacy ICON support is manageable through a mix of US-channel
        and aftermarket sourcing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Electrolux refrigerator failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Pattern data from running Electrolux refrigerator service across LA. Six clusters cover most of the
        dispatch. The shared Electrolux-Frigidaire platform means our diagnostic patterns carry between the sibling
        brands; service order is consistent.
      </p>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Perfect Temp drawer symptom — meat freezing or produce wilting</h3>
        <p>
          The signature Electrolux Perfect Temp full-width drawer holds electronic-controlled temperature across
          its range, and when the sensor drifts or the airflow baffle frosts, the drawer misses setpoint while
          the main compartment reads fine. Diagnostic order: verify drawer-mode setpoint, read sensor via
          Electrolux service interface, inspect airflow baffle for frost, check drain routing. Sensor replacement
          $180–$320; airflow baffle service $160–$260.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Water dispenser not flowing — fill valve or filter path</h3>
        <p>
          Common LA service call. Water dispenser produces no flow or trickle. Usual cause chain: scaled fill
          valve (hard-water LA neighborhoods), expired or clogged water filter, or stuck dispenser solenoid. We
          test inlet pressure, inspect filter, verify valve operation, check dispenser switch. Fill-valve
          replacement $240–$360; dispenser solenoid $180–$280; filter replacement (standard homeowner-installable)
          $40–$80 parts.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Ice-maker mineral buildup — same LA hard-water story</h3>
        <p>
          Ice production drops over 6–12 months in Encino, Sherman Oaks, Tarzana, Calabasas, Pasadena. Standard
          descaling plus fill-valve service resolves most. Electrolux revised ice-maker modules on several French
          Door SKUs in 2018–2020 with better scale tolerance; revised-module swap on earlier-gen units occasionally
          worth considering for heavy-ice households. Standard service $280–$440; module replacement $420–$620.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Compressor start / run capacitor failure on 8–12 year units</h3>
        <p>
          Electrolux and Frigidaire shared-platform compressors use standard start/run capacitor architectures that
          occasionally fail on units age 8–12 years. Symptom: compressor won't start, starts and stops repeatedly,
          or trips a breaker. Meter the capacitor, swap from truck stock. Capacitor service $180–$280.
          Occasionally a failed capacitor signals compressor wear beneath — we verify the compressor health during
          the capacitor service.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Main control board on newer electronic-display units</h3>
        <p>
          2015+ Electrolux French Door units with electronic displays and connected features occasionally throw
          control-board faults — display dimming, setpoint drift, connected-feature failures. Firmware update
          first (resolves some cases); control-board replacement if firmware doesn't clear. $440–$720 for board
          replacement.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>ICON legacy trim and hardware — discontinued-tier sourcing</h3>
        <p>
          Electrolux ICON (discontinued ~2020) installations from 2008–2019 era occasionally need trim or handle
          hardware that's end-of-production. Refrigeration-cycle and sealed-system parts still available through
          Electrolux's US channel; ICON-exclusive aesthetic components require aftermarket or secondary-supplier
          sourcing with longer lead times. We're transparent about this before authorizing parts-heavy ICON
          service — some old-ICON repairs don't pencil vs. replacing the unit.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Electrolux US refrigerator lines we service</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        US Electrolux refrigeration lineup spans current Counter-Depth French Door plus the legacy ICON tier.
        Platform sharing with Frigidaire (mass-market) and Frigidaire Professional (mid-tier) under the same AB
        Electrolux parent.
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Counter-Depth French Door (current)</h3>
          <p>36-inch and 33-inch widths. French Door upper, freezer drawer lower, Perfect Temp full-width drawer,
          water dispenser and ice-maker on select SKUs. Flagship of the current Electrolux US residential line.
          Common in post-2018 kitchen renovations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Full-Depth French Door</h3>
          <p>Deeper traditional French Door configuration with larger internal capacity. Similar Perfect Temp and
          water-dispenser features. Common in larger entertaining kitchens.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Side-by-Side</h3>
          <p>Electrolux Side-by-Side refrigerator with in-door ice and water dispenser. Shared-platform compressor
          and sealed-system architecture with Frigidaire Professional Side-by-Side equivalents.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Electrolux ICON (discontinued, legacy installed base)</h3>
          <p>Premium-premium tier above standard Electrolux, discontinued ~2020. Counter-Depth French Door with
          upgraded trim and stainless. Still serviceable on refrigeration-side components; ICON-specific aesthetic
          parts have limited availability.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Perfect Temp full-width drawer (signature feature)</h3>
          <p>Electronic temperature-controlled drawer spanning full cabinet width, 28°F to 42°F range. Dedicated
          sensor, airflow, and on some SKUs defrost routing. Signature Electrolux feature — service-differentiating
          from Frigidaire Professional equivalents.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Shared-platform sibling brands</h3>
          <p>We service Frigidaire and Frigidaire Professional refrigerators on the same team training — see our
          <a href="/brands/frigidaire-refrigerator-repair/">Frigidaire refrigerator repair</a> page for the mass-
          market sibling. Cross-compatible knowledge and parts sourcing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Electrolux vs Bosch vs KitchenAid — the mid-premium refrigerator tier</h2>
      <p>
        Electrolux sits in a distinct tier — above mass-market (Frigidaire, Whirlpool), below true luxury built-in
        (Sub-Zero, Miele, Thermador). The peer tier includes Bosch 500/800 Series, KitchenAid, certain GE Profile
        configurations. Our techs service the whole mid-premium tier; here's the positioning.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Bosch</b> — BSH German parent, 500 and 800 Series lineup. Strong on quiet operation and compact European-
        influenced form factors. See <a href="/brands/bosch-refrigerator-repair/">Bosch refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>KitchenAid</b> — Whirlpool premium tier. French Door and built-in column options. See
        <a href="/brands/kitchenaid-refrigerator-repair/">KitchenAid refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Electrolux</b> — Swedish parent, Frigidaire platform sharing, Perfect Temp full-width drawer signature,
        strong energy-efficiency positioning. Service advantage: Electrolux-Frigidaire platform sharing means
        parts are broadly available and pricing is competitive. Best pick when the household wants premium features
        at mid-premium pricing and doesn't need the built-in luxury-tier architecture.
      </p>
      <p>
        None is objectively better; they're positioned differently. Electrolux's specific strengths are Perfect
        Temp and the Swedish-heritage energy-efficiency philosophy. Our team services the whole tier equally.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>What Electrolux refrigerator repair costs in LA</h2>
      <p class="intro">Parts pricing is in line with other mid-premium US brands; Electrolux-Frigidaire shared
      platform means the US parts channel is broad and generally well-stocked. Residential diagnostic $89, waived
      with repair.</p>
      <table class="price-table">
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Flat, waived if repair is authorized same visit</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket (French Door)</td><td>$220 – $400</td><td>Standard French Door profile</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket (Counter-Depth built-in-style)</td><td>$260 – $440</td><td>Slightly taller, tighter reveal</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Perfect Temp drawer sensor / airflow</td><td>$180 – $320</td><td>Electrolux service interface diagnostic</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Water dispenser fill valve</td><td>$240 – $360</td><td>Hard-water LA households</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Dispenser solenoid replacement</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>Dispenser-lever no-flow symptoms</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ice-maker fill valve + descaling</td><td>$280 – $440</td><td>Hard-water neighborhoods</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ice-maker module replacement</td><td>$420 – $620</td><td>Revised-module on pre-2018 units</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor start / run capacitor</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>8–12 year unit common service</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Condenser fan motor replacement</td><td>$260 – $440</td><td>Common Electrolux amperage specs</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Evaporator fan / defrost heater</td><td>$240 – $480</td><td>Defrost cycle faults</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Main control board replacement</td><td>$440 – $720</td><td>Post-firmware diagnosis</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor replacement (post-warranty)</td><td>$900 – $1,600</td><td>Shared Electrolux-Frigidaire platform</td></tr>
      </table>
      <p class="small">
        Broader refrigerator cost reference: our <a href="/price-list/refrigerator-repair-cost/">refrigerator repair
        cost guide</a>. Service hub: <a href="/services/refrigerator-repair/">refrigerator repair</a>. Shared-
        platform sibling brand: <a href="/brands/frigidaire-refrigerator-repair/">Frigidaire refrigerator repair</a>.
        Electrolux dishwasher, laundry, and cooking repair covered on sibling pages — see the Electrolux
        <a href="/brands/electrolux/">brand hub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>LA service areas — where our Electrolux calls come from</h2>
      <div class="area-grid">
        <div>
          <h4>Westside (premium kitchen renovations)</h4>
          <p><a href="/beverly-hills/">Beverly Hills</a> · <a href="/brentwood/">Brentwood</a> · <a href="/santa-monica/">Santa Monica</a> · <a href="/west-hollywood/">West Hollywood</a> · Bel Air</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>San Fernando Valley</h4>
          <p><a href="/encino/">Encino</a> · Sherman Oaks · Tarzana · Calabasas · Woodland Hills · Studio City</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>San Gabriel Valley</h4>
          <p><a href="/pasadena/">Pasadena</a> · San Marino · South Pasadena · La Cañada · Arcadia · Glendale</p>
